Installation
------------
1. install node
2. install npm globally
3. install sails (either). npm install sails
4. install bower (npm install bower), create bower file (bower init), Start installing FRONT END components. Bower installs
   its components in bower_components
5. A


Configuration
-------------
1. Set grunt to copy files from assets to .tmp (this happens only when sails is lifted)
2. set grunt to copy files from bower_components to .tmp
3. use the syntax <!--STYLES--><!--STYLES END--> in index.html <head></head>  to so that grunt can embed css fles in header
4. use the syntax <!--SCRIPTS--><!--SCRIPTS END--> in index.html before </body>  to so that grunt can embed js fles in header
5. check the sorting of your libraries in tasks/pipeline.js (change accordingly)
6. create routes for rest apis (/api/v0.0.1/) in config/routes.js

FROND-END
---------
angular libraries https://code.angularjs.org/1.4.3/
angular docs https://docs.angularjs.org/api/
angular famous modules http://ngmodules.org/

angular, angular-touch, angular-resource, angular-ui-router, angular-...

Remove the # from the URL (in app.js in config put $locationProvider.html5Mode(true);)


- Do not use CSRF
- Blueprints: rest = true
- In config directory put a file with module.exports.[name] and then the [name] could be accessed from anywhere in our applications

